                                    "score": 1.0,
                                    "content": "The benefits of RAS blockade have been less studied in patients with diabetes and CKD without hypertension. Although the IDNT$^{13}$ and IRMA-2$^{11}$ studies recruited exclusively patients with T2D and hypertension, a small percentage (3.5%) of patients in the RENNAAL trial, and 30.9% (163 of 527) of randomized patients in the INNOVATION study were normotensive, suggesting that use of RAS blockade may be beneficial in patients without hypertension.$^{12,14}$ Moreover, due to the strong correlation between the severity of albuminuria and the risk of kidney failure in this",
                                    "type": "text"
                                }
                            ]
                        }
